{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d2b1e16a-5414-4889-98f9-ff711812a870","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x switched the default test runner from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.** This means your test project now builds as a standalone executable that `vstest.console` can't discover.\n\n**Two options to fix your CI:**\n\n1. **Update your pipeline** to use `dotnet test` (or run the test executable directly) — this is the recommended path forward:\n   ```\n   dotnet test MyTests.csproj\n   ```\n\n2. **Opt back into VSTest** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is preferred since Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the future direction and offers better performance and parallelism.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0861e0c9-7177-4780-83d8-e804d5576083","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 and MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0 regarding test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes. Let me answer based on what I know.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4 (or around that version), Microsoft began transitioning from the VSTest runner to the Microsoft.Testing.Platform (also known as the \"new test platform\" or \"Microsoft Testing Platform\"). \n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the default runner was VSTest, but you could opt into Microsoft.Testing.Platform. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the default changed - Microsoft.Testing.Platform became the default runner, and VSTest support was essentially dropped or made opt-out.\n\n\nThe core issue is that version 4.x switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default, which produces a standalone executable that doesn't integrate with vstest.console anymore. If your CI pipeline depends on vstest.console for test discovery and execution, it'll fail because the test assembly no longer supports that runner by default. You can either migrate to `dotnet test` or add `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` to your project file to restore VSTest compatibility.\n\nLet me look at what's in the working directory to understand the setup better.","outputTokens":550,"requestId":"7C17:A8FAA:2D8E28A:32B726D:69F960B1"},"id":"d8416035-5b04-40d4-a69a-1fcaffd1b784","timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:15:09.516Z","parentId":"71538d9c-e393-4219-88bd-9cccaf91711b"}
